The article is a speech given by Vice President Kamala Harris in Chicago, Illinois. Harris thanks Governor J.B. Pritzker for his leadership and talks about the importance of the upcoming election. She highlights the accomplishments of the Democratic Party, including providing relief during the pandemic, passing the Inflation Reduction Act, expanding background checks for gun purchases, canceling student debt, and investing in infrastructure and the judiciary. Harris also emphasizes the importance of protecting women's rights, voting rights, and LGBTQ rights. She urges the audience to vote for Democrats and mentions the need to defend the majority in Congress and expand it in the Senate. Harris expresses her commitment to breaking the filibuster on voting rights and reproductive rights. She concludes by quoting Coretta Scott King and encouraging people to vote in the upcoming election.